<div id="review_478165919" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/478165919" />
    <a title="Frank" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7620837-frank"><img alt="Frank" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442852163p2/7620837.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/478165919?book_show_action=true">Dec 15, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Frank" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Frank" href="/user/show/7620837-frank">Frank</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7620837-frank?shelf=crime-thrillers-mystery">crime-thrillers-mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer478165919" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15336069393221773552">Another good thriller from Preston/Child. I always enjoy their books and this one is no exception. This is a combination sci-fi/thriller/western. It includes elements of all of these genres including the main story of the development of a way to change the human genome to eliminate the possibility of getting the flu. Well, this is all good, right? But along the way a nasty mutant flu virus is manufactured that could wipe out mankind (shades of <i>The Stand</i> by Stephen King). This virus came about th</span>
  <span id="freeText15336069393221773552" style="display:none">Another good thriller from Preston/Child. I always enjoy their books and this one is no exception. This is a combination sci-fi/thriller/western. It includes elements of all of these genres including the main story of the development of a way to change the human genome to eliminate the possibility of getting the flu. Well, this is all good, right? But along the way a nasty mutant flu virus is manufactured that could wipe out mankind (shades of <i>The Stand</i> by Stephen King). This virus came about through a corporation, GeneDyne that also developed an artificial blood called <i>PurBlood</i> (shades of <i>True Blood</i>?). Thrown in with this is a chase across the New Mexican desert and a possible lost treasure. Overall, I would recommend this one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15336069393221773552" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


