<div id="review_2513296652" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2513296652" />
    <a title="Chuck Engelhardt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2656025-chuck-engelhardt"><img alt="Chuck Engelhardt" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1339296873p2/2656025.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2513296652?book_show_action=true">Aug 30, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chuck Engelhardt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chuck Engelhardt" href="/user/show/2656025-chuck-engelhardt">Chuck Engelhardt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2513296652" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15595954291959523672">A friend of mind shared <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/39032.Mount_Dragon' title='Mount Dragon by Douglas Preston' rel='nofollow noopener'> Mount Dragon</a> with me as the latest from <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/12577.Douglas_Preston' title='Douglas Preston' rel='nofollow noopener'> Douglas Preston</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/11091.Lincoln_Child' title='Lincoln Child' rel='nofollow noopener'> Lincoln Child</a>. We agree this is probably not their best work, it is nonetheless an interesting tale. It took me a while to get over that the main character wasn&apos;t Jeremy Logan or Gideon Crew, but Guy Carson grew on me as the story developed.<br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/39032.Mount_Dragon' title='Mount Dragon by Douglas Preston' rel='nofollow noopener'> Mount Dragon</a> has a similar feel to other Preston and Child books, but that&apos;s OK with me because I enjoy their stories. They take the readers to interesting places where we</span>
  <span id="freeText15595954291959523672" style="display:none">A friend of mind shared <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/39032.Mount_Dragon" title="Mount Dragon by Douglas Preston" rel="nofollow noopener"> Mount Dragon</a> with me as the latest from <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/12577.Douglas_Preston" title="Douglas Preston" rel="nofollow noopener"> Douglas Preston</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/11091.Lincoln_Child" title="Lincoln Child" rel="nofollow noopener"> Lincoln Child</a>. We agree this is probably not their best work, it is nonetheless an interesting tale. It took me a while to get over that the main character wasn't Jeremy Logan or Gideon Crew, but Guy Carson grew on me as the story developed.<br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/39032.Mount_Dragon" title="Mount Dragon by Douglas Preston" rel="nofollow noopener"> Mount Dragon</a> has a similar feel to other Preston and Child books, but that's OK with me because I enjoy their stories. They take the readers to interesting places where we meet a variety of people with incredible knowledge. With that said, the book and story aren't entirely predictable, but if you've read much from Preston and Child, many of the surprises won't be surprises at all.<br /><br />I thought this was a new book when I read it and wrote the above review, and I just noticed that it's been around a long time. Doesn't change my opinion, but it does explain why it felt a little like a step backwards.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15595954291959523672" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


